   - No missing information if you provide the yearly case data, assuming the data includes the "year" and "cases" for each entry.

Additionally, the query mentions analyzing trends over 5 years but mistakenly asks for incidence rates for the same period. The function for calculating incidence rates only accepts a time period of "1 year," "2 years," "5 years," or "10 years."

To proceed, please provide the "population_size" for the East Africa region and confirm or correct the time period for calculating incidence rates.
<|end|>


